{"questionId":"11816","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate the solution to a coupled system of differential equations when there is only one eigenvalue.</p>\n<p>It is desired to solve the coupled system of differential equations</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot x = 3x + y\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot y =&nbsp; - x + y.\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The general solution to the coupled system of differential equations is hence given by</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  x \\\\   y  \\end{array}} \\right) = A\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  1 \\\\   { - 1}  \\end{array}} \\right){e^{2t}} + B\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  t \\\\   { - t + 1}  \\end{array}} \\right){e^{2t}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>y</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>t</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mi>t</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>As&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t \\to \\infty \">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">→</mo>\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi>\n</math></span> the trajectory approaches an asymptote.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the direction of the trajectory, including the quadrant it is in as it approaches this asymptote.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Will approach the asymptote in the 4th quadrant, moving away from the origin. &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11816","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.2f.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the direction of the trajectory, including the quadrant it is in as it approaches this asymptote.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}